## Known Issues

| ID | Area | Description | Status |
|---|---|---|---|
| RET-010 | Structured planner | Ranking balance for phrases like "executing broker" in long descriptions. | Mitigated via synonyms.json |
| CODE-005 | xml_serializer.py | Function-level state (`_all_rows`, `_files_seen`) for cross-file buffering — corrupts silently on crash. | ⏳ Pending |
| CODE-008 | ui_app.py | Collection management UI still uses Qdrant REST API (get_qdrant_collections, get_collection_stats, delete_qdrant_collection). Needs migration to PostgreSQL. | ⏳ Phase 3 follow-up |
| CODE-009 | ui_app.py | Force re-ingest does not always delete existing DB rows before re-inserting — stale data can persist. | ⏳ Pending |
| CODE-010 | ingestion | Collection name mismatch between UI and PostgreSQL collections table causes ForeignKeyViolation on ingest. Collections should be created in DB when created in UI. | ⏳ Pending |
| CODE-011 | schema_loader.py | Schema files stored on disk (`schemas/`) — should be migrated to PostgreSQL schemas table for consistency. | ⏳ Pending |

**Retired issues (resolved):**
- RET-011 — FIX-01 enum suppression: fixed in Phase 1
- CODE-001 — `scroll(limit=5000)`: eliminated by BM25/pgvector in Phase 2
- CODE-002 — hardcoded collection name: eliminated in retrieval package
- CODE-003 — Qdrant client at import time: eliminated — db_retrieval.py connects lazily
- CODE-004 — `run_query_with_method` / `route_query` overlap: resolved in router.py
- CODE-007 — collection state JSON: eliminated — ingestion state now in PostgreSQL `files` table

